#Text=Coming into this game the Los Angeles Clippers ( 5 - 4 ) had won eight straight versus the Phoenix Suns ( 4 - 4 ) but fell short Thursday night by a score of 118 - 104 .

#Text=The Clippers have now lost four of their last five games The game started out close but Phoenix jumped out to a 20 point lead with a strong third quarter which the Clippers could not recover from .
#Text=The Clippers were missing their starting back court as Chris Paul sat out with a sore right groin while J.J.
#Text=Redick sat out with back spasms .
#Text=The news only got worse for the Clippers as Blake Griffin was ejected after recieving his second technical foul near the end of the first half .
#Text=Griffin played only 16 minutes and came up with 11 points , along with three rebounds and four assists .
#Text=DeAndre Jordan was relatively quiet with only 11 points and nine rebounds .
#Text=Jamal Crawford did his best to fill the offensive void by chipping in a team high 18 points on 7 - 14 shooting , while also nabbing three steals .
#Text=Wesley Johnson played 24 minutes off the bench and continued his good start to the season with 14 points , including 3 - 6 shooting from deep .
#Text=The Phoenix back court duo of Brandon Knight and Eric Bledsoe is steadily becomming one of the most dangerous in the league .
#Text=Knight had a stellar game for the Suns , scoring 37 points on 14 - 22 shooting , including going 6 - 10 from deep .
#Text=He also dished four assists .
#Text=Meanwhile , Bledsoe once again came very close to a triple double with 26 points , 10 rebounds and nine assists and has been looking great so far this season .
#Text=The only other players to score double digits for the Suns were Jon Leuer who had 10 points and 11 rebounds , and T.J.
#Text=Warren who scored 18 points on 7 - 10 shooting .
#Text=The Suns as a team shot a strong 53 percent and did a good job on the defensive glass , not allowing the Clippers any second chances in this game .
#Text=Next up the Nuggets will be in town Saturday to visit the Suns .
#Text=This will be a must win type of game for Phoenix if they hope to see the play - offs this season .
#Text=The Clippers , on the other hand , will look to turn things around at home against Detroit on Saturday , in what will be no easy task as Detroit has been looking very good so far .
#Text=The match up of Andre Drummond versus DeAndre Jordan will be one to watch .
